item.description:
It is a rule that you cannot start a sentence with a present form of the verb съм (&ldquo;to be&rdquo;). When you omit the subject personal Pronoun, the verb has to move into the second position:
&ldquo;Аз съм мъж&rdquo; or &ldquo;Мъж съм&rdquo; – I am a man It is incorrect to say: &ldquo;съм мъж&rdquo;
